member.example:

class Form
{
  [Query("-", "dontlog")]
  public string password { get; }
}

will result in the encoded form having a field named dontlog-password.


interface IServerApi
{
  [Get("/expenses")]
  Task addExpense([Query(Format="0.00")] double expense);
}

Calling serverApi.addExpense(5) will result in a URI of {baseUri}/expenses?expense=5.00.

member.remarks:
By default  disposes the request content once the request is sent, so the body cannot
be read back from the exception (see issue #1189). Enabling this buffers the body into memory before sending;
avoid it for large or streamed uploads.
